### **9. Summary of Consistency Models (The "Google" Deep-Dive)**
*   **Strong Consistency:** Users always see the latest write (Slowest, most correct).
*   **Eventual Consistency:** Users might see old data for a few seconds (Fastest).
*   **Read-Your-Writes:** A user always sees their *own* update, even if others don't yet.
*   **Monotonic Reads:** Once you see a certain version of data, you never "go back in time."

### **10. Back-of-the-Envelope Math (The "Google" Filter)**
*   **100 Million Daily Users (DAU)** $\times$ **100 Requests/Day** $\approx$ **1,150 QPS (Queries Per Second)**.
*   **Storage:** 1 billion messages $\times$ 100 bytes/message $\approx$ **100GB of raw storage**.
*   **Latency:** RAM access (100ns) is **100,000x faster** than Disk access (10ms).